<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Seventh session  
Agenda item 3 
</p>
<p><b>PROMOTION AND PROTECTION OF ALL HUMAN RIGHTS, CIVIL, 
POLITICAL, ECONOMIC, SOCIAL AND CULTURAL RIGHTS, 
            INCLUDING THE RIGHT TO DEVELOPMENT 
</b></p>
<p><b>Albania</b>*<b>, Argentina</b>*<b>, Armenia</b>*<b>, Austria</b>*<b>, Belgium</b>*<b>, Bolivia, Bosnia and 
Herzegovina, Brazil, Bulgaria</b>*<b>, Chile</b>*<b>, Croatia</b>*<b>, Czech Republic</b>*<b>, Cyprus, 
Estonia</b>*<b>, Finland</b>*<b>,</b> <b>France, Georgia</b>*<b>, Germany, Guatemala, Hungary</b>*<b>, 
Japan, Luxembourg</b>*<b>, Maldives</b>*<b>, Mexico, Montenegro</b>*<b>, Peru, Portugal</b>*<b>, 
Slovakia</b>*<b>, Slovenia, Spain</b>*<b>, The former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia</b>*<b>, 
Ukraine, Uruguay :  draft resolution  
</b></p>
<p><b>7/... International Convention for the Protection of All Persons 
from Enforced Disappearance 
</b></p>
<p><i>The Human Rights Council</i>, </p>
<p><i> Recalling </i>General Assembly resolution 47/133 of 18 December 1992, by which the 
Assembly adopted the Declaration on the Protection of All Persons from Enforced 
Disappearances, 
</p>
<p><i> Recalling</i> its resolution 1/1 of 29 June 2006, 
</p>
<p>     
</p>
<p>*  Non-member State of the Human Rights Council. </p>

 <p></p>
<p><i> Acknowledging</i> the adoption by the Assembly of the International Convention for the 
Protection of All Persons from Enforced Disappearance in its resolution 61/177 of 20 December 
2006, and its opening for signature, ratification and accession, 
</p>
<p><i> Welcoming </i>the signing of the Convention by 57 States at the opening ceremony, held in 
Paris, on 6 February 2007, and the signing of the Convention thereafter, 
</p>
<p><i> Recognizing</i> that the entry into force of the Convention as soon as possible, through its 
ratification by 20 States, will be a significant event,  
</p>
<p> 1.<i> Commends</i> those States that have already ratified the International Convention for 
the Protection of All Persons from Enforced Disappearance and therefore have become States 
parties to this instrument; 
</p>
<p> 2<i>.  Encourages</i> States that are in the process of signing, ratifying or acceding to the 
Convention to complete their internal procedures towards this aim in compliance with domestic 
legislation; 
</p>
<p> 3<i>. Calls on </i>all States to sign, ratify or accede to the Convention; 
</p>
<p> 4. <i>Encourages</i> States to join, on a voluntary basis, the widespread campaign engaged 
by the Group of Friends of the Convention, in order to share information on best practices and to 
work towards the early coming into force of the Convention with the aim of its universality. 
</p>
